while he was last seen smashing a racquet after cramp foiled a potential US Open upset of Richard Gasquet , Kokkinakis has been defended staunchly by Healy .
the teenager is currently in Glasgow , competing with Sam Groth for the second singles berth behind Bernard Tomic in the Davis Cup semi-final against Britain .
" one thing I do feel quite keenly about is I think Thanasi 's been dragged into the fray a little bit , " Healy said .
he did break a racquet when he lost when he cramped in the US , but he is not the first player to break a racquet out of frustration with himself , and I know Thanasi well enough to know he would not be proud of that .
but , really , he is handled himself extremely well , in pretty provocative circumstances in the US with Harrison and so on , and I think he deserves a lot of credit .
he is a great team around him , he is got a great family around him and I just think he is been a little hard done by .
he is a very mature 19-year-old , he works very hard , and he fits in with the team and so on , he has not ever had an issue with the other players , he is well respected in the locker room , he trains hard , he is in great shape , he is a very stable and mature young guy and I just think he deserves to be judged on his own merits .
